# Kubernetes Basics Lab (Minikube + kubectl) — Ubuntu

## PHASE 1 — INSTALL REQUIRED PACKAGES

### Step 1 — Update Ubuntu Packages

```bash
sudo apt update
```

# Refreshes Ubuntu package list

---

### Step 2 — Install Dependencies

```bash
sudo apt install curl wget apt-transport-https -y
```

# Installs required packages

---

## PHASE 2 — INSTALL kubectl

### Step 3 — Download kubectl

```bash
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
```

# Downloads latest kubectl binary

---

### Step 4 — Give Execute Permission + Move to System Path

```bash
chmod +x kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/
```

# Makes kubectl executable and globally accessible

---

### Step 5 — Verify kubectl Installation

```bash
kubectl version --client
```

# Displays kubectl version

---

## PHASE 3 — INSTALL MINIKUBE

### Step 6 — Download Minikube

```bash
curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
```

# Downloads Minikube binary

---

### Step 7 — Install Minikube

```bash
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube
```

# Installs Minikube globally

---

## PHASE 4 — START DOCKER

### Step 8 — Start Docker

```bash
sudo systemctl start docker
```

# Starts Docker service

---

## PHASE 5 — START KUBERNETES CLUSTER

### Step 9 — Start Minikube Cluster

```bash
minikube start --driver=docker
```

# Starts local Kubernetes cluster using Docker

---

### Step 10 — Verify Nodes

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```

# Displays cluster nodes

---

### Step 11 — Check Minikube Status

```bash
minikube status
```

# Displays Minikube cluster status

---

## PHASE 6 — CREATE POD

### Step 12 — Create Nginx Pod

```bash
kubectl run my-nginx --image=nginx
```

# Creates nginx Pod

---

### Step 13 — Check Pods

```bash
kubectl get pods
```

# Displays pod status

---

### Step 14 — Describe Pod

```bash
kubectl describe pod my-nginx
```

# Displays detailed pod information

---

## PHASE 7 — DEBUG POD

### Step 15 — View Pod Logs

```bash
kubectl logs my-nginx
```

# Displays container logs

---

## PHASE 8 — EXPOSE POD USING NODEPORT

### Step 16 — Expose Pod

```bash
kubectl expose pod my-nginx --type=NodePort --port=80
```

# Creates NodePort service

---

### Step 17 — View Services

```bash
kubectl get services
```

# Displays services

---

### Step 18 — Get Browser URL

```bash
minikube service my-nginx --url
```

# Displays application access URL

---

## PHASE 9 — CREATE DEPLOYMENT

### Step 19 — Create Deployment

```bash
kubectl create deployment my-dep --image=nginx --replicas=2
```

# Creates deployment with 2 replicas

---

### Step 20 — Verify Deployment

```bash
kubectl get deployments
```

# Displays deployment status

---

## PHASE 10 — SCALE DEPLOYMENT

### Step 21 — Scale Deployment

```bash
kubectl scale deployment my-dep --replicas=5
```

# Scales deployment to 5 replicas

---

### Step 22 — View All Resources

```bash
kubectl get all
```

# Displays:
# - Pods
# - Services
# - Deployments
# - ReplicaSets

---

## PHASE 11 — OPEN DASHBOARD

### Step 23 — Open Kubernetes Dashboard

```bash
minikube dashboard
```

# Opens Kubernetes dashboard in browser

---

## PHASE 12 — CLEANUP

### Step 24 — Delete Service

```bash
kubectl delete service my-nginx
```

# Deletes service

---

### Step 25 — Delete Deployment

```bash
kubectl delete deployment my-dep
```

# Deletes deployment

---

### Step 26 — Delete Pod

```bash
kubectl delete pod my-nginx
```

# Deletes Pod

---

### Step 27 — Stop Minikube

```bash
minikube stop
```

# Stops Kubernetes cluster

---
